# Bivariate choropleth map

x = "2024"
y = "2023-raw"
n = 3 # number of bins per variable

heatIndex_m[x] = pd.to_numeric(heatIndex_m[x], errors="coerce")
impervious_m[y] = pd.to_numeric(impervious_m[y], errors="coerce")

# Quantile bins (0..N-1). duplicates='drop' avoids errors if many ties.
heatIndex_m["x_bin"] = pd.qcut(heatIndex_m[x], n, labels=False, duplicates="drop")
impervious_m["y_bin"] = pd.qcut(impervious_m[y], n, labels=False, duplicates="drop")

# Combine bins into one class ID (row-major)
heatIndex_m["bi_class"] = impervious_m["y_bin"] * n + heatIndex_m["x_bin"]
In[73]:
# Map classes to colors

# 3x3 bivariate palette (row-major: y from low->high, x from low->high)
palette = [
    "#d3d3d3", "#d9b578", "#df9109",
    "#d58fd9", "#da7b7c", "#e16209",
    "#d810e5", "#dd0e82", "#e40b0a",
]

def class_to_color(v):
    if pd.isna(v):
        return "#dddddd"
    return palette[int(v)]
        
heatIndex_m["bi_color"] = heatIndex_m["bi_class"].apply(class_to_color)

ax = heatIndex_m.plot(color=heatIndex_m["bi_color"], linewidth=0.3, edgecolor="white",
figsize=(9, 7))
ax.set_title(f"Bivariate choropleth: Heat Index {x} (x) vs Impervious Surface Cover {y} (y)")
ax.set_axis_off()
plt.savefig(r"C:\Users\aocro\Documents\Geovis portfolio\Lab5_s4a.png")
plt.show()

# Build a bivariate legend

from matplotlib.patches import Rectangle

fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(4, 4))

for y in range(n):
    for x in range(n):
        idx = y * n + x
        ax.add_patch(Rectangle((x, y), 1, 1, facecolor=palette[idx],
edgecolor="none"))
        
ax.set_xlim(0, n)
ax.set_ylim(0, n)
ax.set_aspect("equal")

# Minimal labeling (edit these to match your variables)
ax.set_xticks([0.5, 1.5, 2.5])
ax.set_yticks([0.5, 1.5, 2.5])
ax.set_xticklabels(["Low", "Med", "High"])
ax.set_yticklabels(["Low", "Med", "High"])
ax.set_xlabel(f"Heat Index (F)")
ax.set_ylabel(f"Impervious Surface Cover (%)")

# Clean look
for spine in ax.spines.values():
    spine.set_visible(False)

plt.title("Bivariate legend (3x3)")

from shapely.affinity import scale

vals = impervious_m[CART_FIELD].to_numpy()
factors = np.sqrt(vals / np.nanmean(vals)) # area is ~factor^2

scaled_geoms = [
    scale(geom, xfact=f, yfact=f, origin="center")
    for geom, f in zip(impervious_m.geometry, factors)
]

gdf_scaled = impervious_m.copy()
gdf_scaled["geometry_scaled"] = scaled_geoms
gdf_scaled = gdf_scaled.set_geometry("geometry_scaled")

ax = gdf_scaled.plot(
    column=CART_FIELD,
    scheme="Quantiles",
    k=5,
    cmap="Reds",
    linewidth=0.3,
    edgecolor="white",
    legend=True,
    figsize=(9, 7),
)
ax.set_title(f"Non-contiguous cartogram (scaled) by {CART_FIELD}")
ax.set_axis_off()
plt.show()

from shapely.affinity import scale

vals = impervious_m[CART_FIELD].to_numpy()
factors = (vals / np.nanmean(vals)) # area is ~factor^2

scaled_geoms = [
    scale(geom, xfact=f, yfact=f, origin="center")
    for geom, f in zip(impervious_m.geometry, factors)
]

gdf_scaled = impervious_m.copy()
gdf_scaled["geometry_scaled"] = scaled_geoms
gdf_scaled = gdf_scaled.set_geometry("geometry_scaled")

ax = gdf_scaled.plot(
    column=CART_FIELD,
    scheme="Quantiles",
    k=5,
    cmap="Reds",
    linewidth=0.3,
    edgecolor="white",
    legend=True,
    figsize=(9, 7),
)
